The author describes their experience as a White House intern during the signing of the Executive Order on Reviving the National Space Council. They mention the presence of President Trump, Vice President Pence, and astronauts Buzz Aldrin, David Wolf, and Alvin Drew. The author reflects on their childhood fascination with space and their interest in aerospace engineering. They express excitement about pursuing a degree in engineering and mention their participation in the Summer 2017 White House Internship Program.